12:32.033 --> 12:34.700
If something miraculous,
really kind of movie-like

12:34.700 --> 12:36.500
could happen here,

12:36.500 --> 12:41.166
where we could all kind of send
love and--and truth

12:41.166 --> 12:42.467
and a kind of sanity

12:42.467 --> 12:46.100
to Deng Xiaoping
right now in Beijing

12:46.100 --> 12:47.233
that he will take his troops

12:47.233 --> 12:49.233
and take the Chinese away
from Tibet

12:49.233 --> 12:50.734
and allow these people to live

12:50.734 --> 12:52.834
as free independent people
again.

12:52.834 --> 12:54.900
[applause]

12:56.734 --> 12:58.767
So.

12:58.767 --> 13:00.734
Thoughts.
We send these thoughts.

13:00.734 --> 13:03.567
Send this thought out.
Send this thought.

13:03.567 --> 13:05.200
- "We send this thought.

13:05.200 --> 13:07.200
"We send it out right now--
oh, you know what?

13:07.200 --> 13:09.000
"I'm sorry.
There's been a mistake.

13:09.000 --> 13:10.800
"The thoughts are actually
supposed to be sent

13:10.800 --> 13:12.467
"to the producers
of 'Moonlight.'

13:12.467 --> 13:13.500
"Uh, this is not a joke.

13:13.500 --> 13:16.133
"'Moonlight,'
these thoughts are for you.

13:16.133 --> 13:19.033
"There's been
a horrible mistake.

13:19.033 --> 13:22.133
'Moonlight,' take the thoughts."

13:22.133 --> 13:24.667
But--
but there is a lot about Tibet

13:24.667 --> 13:26.033
that you might not
actually know.

13:26.033 --> 13:28.567
For a start, it's larger
than you probably think.

13:28.567 --> 13:31.934
China say it's this area,
but Tibetan exiles will say

13:31.934 --> 13:34.066
it's even larger,
encompassing an area

13:34.066 --> 13:36.233
that is roughly 1/4 of China,

13:36.233 --> 13:38.900
so it's very big
in a confusing way,

13:38.900 --> 13:40.100
which, and this is true,

13:40.100 --> 13:42.166
is also how
director Lars von Trier

13:42.166 --> 13:44.633
characterized
Willem Dafoe's dick.

13:44.633 --> 13:46.834
Seriously, he told reporters,

13:46.834 --> 13:48.066
"It's too big.

13:48.066 --> 13:51.667
Everybody got very confused
when they saw it."

13:51.667 --> 13:52.934
What I'm saying is,

13:52.934 --> 13:55.834
Tibet is the Willem Dafoe's dick
of Planet Earth.

13:55.834 --> 13:58.567
It is surprisingly large.

13:58.567 --> 13:59.667
The point is,

13:59.667 --> 14:02.200
China invaded Tibet in 1950,

14:02.200 --> 14:04.233
and ever since,
they've imposed strict controls

14:04.233 --> 14:06.166
on the institutions
of Tibetan Buddhism there.

14:06.166 --> 14:07.967
Temples and monasteries
have been destroyed,

14:07.967 --> 14:10.800
and hundreds of thousands
of Tibetans have been killed,

14:10.800 --> 14:13.367
and things inside Tibet
are still grim.

14:13.367 --> 14:15.500
When Freedom House scored
countries and territories

14:15.500 --> 14:17.333
for political rights
and civil liberties,

14:17.333 --> 14:19.633
Tibet came in second-worst,

14:19.633 --> 14:21.166
behind Syria

14:21.166 --> 14:24.567
and ahead of both Somalia
and North Korea.

14:24.567 --> 14:28.266
The whole territory is
a gross human rights violation,

14:28.266 --> 14:29.767
which is interestingly
another way

14:29.767 --> 14:31.333
that Lars von Trier
has described

14:31.333 --> 14:33.667
Willem Dafoe's penis.

14:33.667 --> 14:36.734
And perhaps the clearest sign
of just how bad conditions are

14:36.734 --> 14:38.800
is the fact that
since early 2009,

14:38.800 --> 14:43.300
146 Tibetans have self-immolated
in Tibet and China,

14:43.300 --> 14:46.000
setting themselves on fire
in protest,

14:46.000 --> 14:49.600
to which the Chinese police
have been less than sympathetic.

14:49.600 --> 14:52.633
[unintelligible yelling]

15:15.000 --> 15:18.533
- Well, every part of that
is fucking horrifying,

15:18.533 --> 15:21.734
and China is unlikely to loosen
its grip on the region.

15:21.734 --> 15:23.500
Tibet has
incredibly rich resources,

15:23.500 --> 15:24.800
from gold and lithium

15:24.800 --> 15:27.100
to rivers supplying
hydroelectric power and water

15:27.100 --> 15:28.667
to over a billion people,

15:28.667 --> 15:30.433
so they are very sensitive

15:30.433 --> 15:32.600
to any perceived threat
to their control,

15:32.600 --> 15:35.400
which brings us back
to the Dalai Lama.

15:35.400 --> 15:39.000
Traditionally, he's been both
a spiritual and political leader

15:39.000 --> 15:40.467
of Tibetan Buddhists,
sort of a cross

15:40.467 --> 15:44.567
between a pope and a president,
a popesident, if you will,

15:44.567 --> 15:46.934
but you shouldn't,
so please don't.

15:46.934 --> 15:48.667
China has done
everything they can

15:48.667 --> 15:50.200
over the years
to diminish his power.

15:50.200 --> 15:53.834
He even fled Tibet in 1959
under fear of arrest,

15:53.834 --> 15:55.433
and he hasn't been back since,

15:55.433 --> 15:57.600
an escape that was reported
at the time

15:57.600 --> 16:00.734
by the most British man
who has ever lived.

16:00.734 --> 16:02.100
- The young Dalai Lama,

16:02.100 --> 16:04.500
revered by his people
as a living Buddha,

16:04.500 --> 16:06.900
was reported under arrest
by the Reds,

16:06.900 --> 16:08.333
but,
according to other sources,

16:08.333 --> 16:09.834
is safely in hiding.

16:09.834 --> 16:11.166
One clear fact:

16:11.166 --> 16:12.900
Red tyranny is not wanted

16:12.900 --> 16:15.200
by these intensely religious
people.

16:15.200 --> 16:18.367
- "Yes, damn that unwanted
creeping Red tyranny,

16:18.367 --> 16:20.967
"down with those thieving
imperialists,

16:20.967 --> 16:22.867
"and good night
to Her Majesty's subjects

16:22.867 --> 16:25.200
"in Bahrain, Maldives,
Rhodesia, Jamaica,

16:25.200 --> 16:27.800
"Barbados, Kenya, and Uganda.

16:27.800 --> 16:30.266
Nighty night.
Sleepy tight."

16:30.266 --> 16:31.600
[cheers and applause]

16:31.600 --> 16:34.700
And so, for over 50 years,

16:34.700 --> 16:37.166
the Dalai Lama has lived
in exile in India,

16:37.166 --> 16:38.600
and he's lived quite a life.

16:38.600 --> 16:40.734
He's met with
the last four presidents,

16:40.734 --> 16:42.834
and when he was a child,
FDR gave him

16:42.834 --> 16:45.567
a beautiful
Patek Philippe pocket watch,

16:45.567 --> 16:47.033
which he still has to this day,

16:47.033 --> 16:50.166
and George W. Bush gave him
an even greater gift

16:50.166 --> 16:54.500
by painting his portrait,
this portrait,

16:54.500 --> 16:56.400
and I give Bush's skills
as an artist

16:56.400 --> 16:59.000
the same review I give
his time as president:

16:59.000 --> 17:01.166
not bad for a five-year-old.

17:01.166 --> 17:03.734
Now, the Dalai Lama
officially stepped down

17:03.734 --> 17:05.934
from running
the Tibetan government in exile

17:05.934 --> 17:07.300
in 2011, but he is still

17:07.300 --> 17:09.900
of profound importance
to the Tibetan people

17:09.900 --> 17:12.300
as a spiritual leader
and a figurehead,

17:12.300 --> 17:13.900
and here, here is where

17:13.900 --> 17:16.300
this story gets
absolutely amazing,

17:16.300 --> 17:17.967
because he's 81 years old,

17:17.967 --> 17:19.800
so thoughts
have inevitably turned

17:19.800 --> 17:21.233
to his next reincarnation,

17:21.233 --> 17:24.333
but it turns out there's a bit
of a problem with that.

17:24.333 --> 17:25.300
Let me explain.

17:25.300 --> 17:28.100
Broadly speaking,
when the Dalai Lama dies,

17:28.100 --> 17:29.934
he reincarnates as a child

17:29.934 --> 17:32.033
somewhere on Earth,
and traditionally,

17:32.033 --> 17:34.133
a key person
in the process of finding him

17:34.133 --> 17:36.333
is someone called
the Panchen Lama,

17:36.333 --> 17:37.800
and when the Panchen Lama dies,

17:37.800 --> 17:40.734
the Dalai Lama plays
a similar role in finding him,

17:40.734 --> 17:41.734
and so on, and so on.

17:41.734 --> 17:44.066
They're basically playing
a Buddhist version

17:44.066 --> 17:45.934
of hide-and-seek.

17:45.934 --> 17:49.000
So the ninth Panchen Lama
helped to identify

17:49.000 --> 17:50.734
the current Dalai Lama,

17:50.734 --> 17:53.900
who in turn identified
this six-year-old boy

17:53.900 --> 17:55.133
as the Panchen Lama,

17:55.133 --> 17:57.266
but this is where it starts
to get tricky,

17:57.266 --> 18:01.400
because that boy has not been
seen in more than 20 years.

18:01.400 --> 18:02.834
- These are
the last known pictures

18:02.834 --> 18:04.200
of Gedhun Choekyi Nyima,

18:04.200 --> 18:06.633
the boy chosen
to be Panchen Lama.

18:06.633 --> 18:09.333
The Chinese authorities
rejected his appointment,

18:09.333 --> 18:11.734
arrested the boy
and his family.

18:11.734 --> 18:12.834
- It's true.

18:12.834 --> 18:14.934
China kidnapped a six-year-old,

18:14.934 --> 18:16.934
and no one has
heard from him since,

18:16.934 --> 18:18.333
although just two years ago,

18:18.333 --> 18:21.467
a senior Chinese official said
he is "being educated,

18:21.467 --> 18:23.900
"living a normal life,
growing up healthily,

18:23.900 --> 18:26.033
and does not wish
to be disturbed,"

18:26.033 --> 18:28.066
which is a little suspicious
'cause it sounds like

18:28.066 --> 18:30.533
the kind of thing
a former child star's publicist

18:30.533 --> 18:32.367
would scream into a phone.

18:32.367 --> 18:34.667
"She's growing up healthy,
living a normal life,

18:34.667 --> 18:36.066
"and those track marks
on her arms

18:36.066 --> 18:38.066
"are just where they inject
the vitamins.

18:38.066 --> 18:41.333
She's fine!
She's fine!"

18:41.333 --> 18:44.633
But China didn't stop at
just stealing the Panchen Lama.

18:44.633 --> 18:46.967
They had another trick
up their sleeve.

18:46.967 --> 18:49.400
- In an attempt to discredit
the Dalai Lama's choice

18:49.400 --> 18:51.834
of one of Tibet's
top Buddhist spiritual leaders,

18:51.834 --> 18:55.066
Chinese officials used
a 200-year-old ceremony

18:55.066 --> 18:57.700
to name their own Panchen Lama.

18:57.700 --> 19:01.834
- Yes, they made
their own fake Panchen Lama.

19:01.834 --> 19:04.467
They basically counterfeited
a religious leader

19:04.467 --> 19:06.500
like a knockoff handbag.

19:06.500 --> 19:10.000
That doesn't say "Coach."
That says "Cough."

19:10.000 --> 19:12.533
And--and China's tactics here
are obvious.

19:12.533 --> 19:14.166
If they control
the Panchen Lama,

19:14.166 --> 19:16.533
they can use him
to pick a new Dalai Lama

19:16.533 --> 19:18.734
who might,
completely coincidentally,

19:18.734 --> 19:21.333
be very favorable
to the Chinese government.

19:21.333 --> 19:24.000
Meanwhile, the Dalai Lama,
understandably,

19:24.000 --> 19:26.433
is pretty pissed off about this.

19:26.433 --> 19:29.467
- The one thing
that I want to make clear

19:29.467 --> 19:34.967
as far as my own rebirth
is concerned,

19:34.967 --> 19:38.967
the final authority is myself.

19:38.967 --> 19:41.734
No one else.

19:41.734 --> 19:44.734
And obviously not
Chinese Communists.

19:44.734 --> 19:45.834
- Yeah.

19:45.834 --> 19:47.900
That is some forceful language
too.

19:47.900 --> 19:49.000
He's basically saying,

19:49.000 --> 19:51.834
"They can make that decision
over my dead body,

19:51.834 --> 19:55.367
except, you know,
specifically not that."

19:55.367 --> 19:57.400
He's now actually saying
that he will either not

19:57.400 --> 19:59.600
reincarnate as the Dalai Lama
at all

19:59.600 --> 20:03.133
or, if he does, it won't be
inside Chinese-controlled Tibet,

20:03.133 --> 20:05.333
it will be somewhere else,
which is incredible

20:05.333 --> 20:07.033
because that means
that when he dies,

20:07.033 --> 20:10.667
we could plausibly wind up
with two rival Dalai Lamas,

20:10.667 --> 20:12.934
and the already fraught
situation in Tibet

20:12.934 --> 20:14.600
could spiral out of control.

20:14.600 --> 20:17.066
And for the time being,
there is really only one person

20:17.066 --> 20:19.100
who can fill you in on
what is happening

20:19.100 --> 20:21.900
in the Dalai Lama's head,
but he lives in India,

20:21.900 --> 20:23.967
and that is
a 14-hour flight away,

20:23.967 --> 20:25.233
and the reason I know that

20:25.233 --> 20:28.233
is I went to speak
to the Dalai Lama in India.

20:28.233 --> 20:29.233
Enjoy.

20:29.233 --> 20:30.266
[cheers and applause]

20:30.266 --> 20:31.834
[Indian music]

20:31.834 --> 20:34.166
Yes, I traveled
to the Himalayan foothills

20:34.166 --> 20:36.000
of Dharamsala, India,

20:36.000 --> 20:38.200
a journey
that involved considerably more

20:38.200 --> 20:39.433
uphill walking,

20:39.433 --> 20:41.200
cows, and monkey traffic

20:41.200 --> 20:42.900
than I'd been led to believe,

20:42.900 --> 20:45.633
all to talk with the Dalai Lama
about China,

20:45.633 --> 20:49.166
conditions in Tibet,
and what comes next for him.

20:49.166 --> 20:51.800
Your Holiness,
it is an honor to speak to you.

20:51.800 --> 20:54.066
May I say, tashi delek.

20:54.066 --> 20:55.500
- Tashi delek.
Thank you.

20:55.500 --> 20:56.900
- How is my pronunciation?

20:56.900 --> 20:58.500
Tashi de--
- I think very good.

20:58.500 --> 21:03.066
- In my defense, I just started
learning Tibetan 40 seconds ago.

21:03.066 --> 21:05.066
- [laughs]

21:05.066 --> 21:06.834
- So let's talk about China.
- Mm.

21:06.834 --> 21:08.300
- Because the Chinese government

21:08.300 --> 21:11.100
absolutely hates you,
don't they?

21:11.100 --> 21:12.333
- Yes.

21:12.333 --> 21:14.433
- Publicly,
one government official said

21:14.433 --> 21:17.100
you're a wolf
wrapped in monk's robes.

21:17.100 --> 21:18.200
- Mm.

21:18.200 --> 21:21.266
- And photos of you
are forbidden in many places.

21:21.266 --> 21:24.333
You don't, to me,
look like an evil wolf.

21:24.333 --> 21:27.033
- [laughs]

21:27.033 --> 21:30.000
They describe me as a demon.

21:30.000 --> 21:32.033
- You're a demon?
Yeah.

21:32.033 --> 21:33.767
- Then I immediately reacted,

21:33.767 --> 21:37.900
"Yes, I'm demon with horn."

21:37.900 --> 21:40.033
- Yeah, 'cause that's
the classic demon, right?

21:40.033 --> 21:40.934
- Yes.

21:40.934 --> 21:42.667
- I think that's--
when they look at you,

21:42.667 --> 21:44.266
that's what they see.

21:44.266 --> 21:47.533
- Oh, whatever they want to see,
that's their freedom.

21:47.533 --> 21:49.767
I have no such--
no negative feeling.

21:49.767 --> 21:53.133
I just feel a laugh, like that.

21:53.133 --> 21:58.667
I practice, you see,
taking others' anger, suspicion,

21:58.667 --> 22:03.900
distrust,
and give them patience,

22:03.900 --> 22:06.734
tolerance, and compassion.

22:06.734 --> 22:07.834
I practice that.

22:07.834 --> 22:10.133
- But it seems
the Chinese government

22:10.133 --> 22:13.133
are particularly good
at taking your positivity,

22:13.133 --> 22:16.266
turning it back into negativity

22:16.266 --> 22:19.166
and oppression
of the Tibetan people,

22:19.166 --> 22:21.266
and they hand it back to you
as it was.

22:21.266 --> 22:22.500
- Yes.

22:22.500 --> 22:24.133
- Just outside
the Dalai Lama's temple

22:24.133 --> 22:26.200
is a local memorial
honoring Tibetans

22:26.200 --> 22:27.834
who've self-immolated
in protest

22:27.834 --> 22:29.533
against Chinese oppression,

22:29.533 --> 22:32.500
acts that put him
in a very difficult position.

22:32.500 --> 22:34.533
This is a hard question.
- Oh.

22:34.533 --> 22:37.233
- The self-immolation
that has happened...

22:37.233 --> 22:38.166
- Oh.

22:38.166 --> 22:40.433
- 140 Tibetans...
- Yes.

22:40.433 --> 22:42.467
- Have burned themselves.

22:42.467 --> 22:43.867
It is very, very sad.

22:43.867 --> 22:45.166
- Indeed, yes.

22:45.166 --> 22:48.700
- Why is it hard for you
to definitively tell them

22:48.700 --> 22:51.166
to stop doing it?

22:51.166 --> 22:54.500
- This is, I find, very
difficult sort of situation.

22:54.500 --> 22:58.834
Right from the beginning,
when I first heard that,

22:58.834 --> 23:02.500
firstly, I express
my sort of sadness.

23:02.500 --> 23:08.000
Then, meantime,
if I say their action is wrong,

23:08.000 --> 23:12.400
then their family, they will--
they feel very sad.

23:12.400 --> 23:14.133
One of their family member

23:14.133 --> 23:18.066
did something
against the Dalai Lama's wish.

23:18.066 --> 23:20.600
- Right.
- I don't want to create that.

23:20.600 --> 23:23.300
Then, certainly,
I cannot support that,

23:23.300 --> 23:24.834
the act of killing.

23:24.834 --> 23:29.433
From Buddhist viewpoint,
self-killing, not good.

23:29.433 --> 23:33.166
So therefore, my position
is very, very difficult,

23:33.166 --> 23:36.433
so then best thing is,
remain silent.

23:36.433 --> 23:38.767
Keep quiet.

23:38.767 --> 23:40.900
- The Dalai Lama
is painfully aware

23:40.900 --> 23:42.600
how powerful his words are,

23:42.600 --> 23:44.633
and he occasionally uses them
in targeted

23:44.633 --> 23:47.400
and sometimes
surprisingly specific ways,

23:47.400 --> 23:48.500
like this example,

23:48.500 --> 23:50.600
which he offered up
out of nowhere.

23:50.600 --> 23:53.567
- One of my previous visit,
Mongolia.

23:53.567 --> 23:56.266
They took lot of vodka.

23:56.266 --> 23:58.633
The Russians sort of
hard philosophy.

23:58.633 --> 23:59.867
- They like a drink.

23:59.867 --> 24:01.233
Yeah.
Vodka.

24:01.233 --> 24:05.967
- Then, I said,
"Drink much less vodka."

24:05.967 --> 24:07.633
- Yeah, they love to hear that.

24:07.633 --> 24:09.900
- Instead of that,
their tradition

24:09.900 --> 24:12.066
is to drink horse milk.

24:12.066 --> 24:14.433
- Wait, hold on.
- Horse milk.

24:14.433 --> 24:17.300
- Wait, you tried
to wean them off vodka

24:17.300 --> 24:18.900
by giving them horse milk?

24:18.900 --> 24:21.300
- Oh, yes.
They--they follow.

24:21.300 --> 24:23.633
- What?
- They follow.

24:23.633 --> 24:28.300
Since then, I think
a majority of Mongolian

24:28.300 --> 24:30.166
no longer any drink.

24:30.166 --> 24:32.900
- Hold on, that is a--
that is a huge claim.

24:32.900 --> 24:35.734
You cured Mongolia
of alcoholism...

24:35.734 --> 24:37.834
- Yes.
- Using horse milk?

24:37.834 --> 24:39.734
- Yes.
- Yeah, not to labor the point--

24:39.734 --> 24:43.233
I'm just concerned I would see
horse milk, and I'd think,

24:43.233 --> 24:45.600
"Oh, that came from a horse."

24:45.600 --> 24:48.100
- This--
- Oh, oh.

24:48.100 --> 24:49.133
- That's illogical.

24:49.133 --> 24:52.300
What's differences,
cow milk and horse milk?

24:52.300 --> 24:53.333
What differences?

24:53.333 --> 24:55.433
- One comes out of a cow.

24:55.433 --> 24:58.533
The other, I don't know
how you get it out of a horse.

24:58.533 --> 25:01.600
- [laughs]

25:02.900 --> 25:04.600
- Finally, we were having fun,

25:04.600 --> 25:07.667
and I knew just how
to keep the party going.

25:07.667 --> 25:10.934
Let's talk about
a lighter subject: death.

25:10.934 --> 25:14.567
You are going to die,
and when you do,

25:14.567 --> 25:16.767
it's going to be
a massive problem

25:16.767 --> 25:20.266
because there are issues
regarding your reincarnation

25:20.266 --> 25:22.233
regarding China.

25:22.233 --> 25:24.834
- I do not match concern
about that.

25:24.834 --> 25:28.500
My main concern is well-being
of 7 billion human being

25:28.500 --> 25:34.066
and then preservation
of rich Buddhist tradition,

25:34.066 --> 25:35.500
which we kept.

25:35.500 --> 25:37.367
- But you're intertwined
with that.

25:37.367 --> 25:38.734
- No, no.
As an individual person,

25:38.734 --> 25:40.066
not much important.

25:40.066 --> 25:41.066
You know.

25:41.066 --> 25:43.367
- Right,
but you're the Dalai Lama.

25:43.367 --> 25:47.033
- But Buddhism,
over 2,600 years,

25:47.033 --> 25:48.867
still very much alive.

25:48.867 --> 25:52.233
- So do you think you might be
the last Dalai Lama?

25:52.233 --> 25:53.233
- Very possible.

25:53.233 --> 25:54.767
- You do?
- Yes.

25:54.767 --> 25:56.667
- You might be it?

25:56.667 --> 25:59.834
- If I become last Dalai Lama,
I feel very happy.

25:59.834 --> 26:01.166
- Why,
because you were a good one?

26:01.166 --> 26:05.333
- Oh, yes, I may say,
quite intelligent.

26:05.333 --> 26:07.133
- Oh, oh, you're calling
yourself intelligent, are you?

26:07.133 --> 26:08.533
- Oh, I think so.

26:08.533 --> 26:11.233
- So a little bit of arrogance
there, as well.

26:11.233 --> 26:14.967
But if you don't resolve
your reincarnation issue,

26:14.967 --> 26:18.433
are you not worried
that China will appoint

26:18.433 --> 26:20.233
their own Dalai Lama

26:20.233 --> 26:24.000
and he may not speak
like you're speaking now?

26:24.000 --> 26:26.400
- That also, if, may I say so?
- Yeah.

26:26.400 --> 26:31.133
- That's also, you see,
one of the foolish act.

26:31.133 --> 26:33.133
Short-sighted.
- China.

26:33.133 --> 26:36.867
- Without using
human brain properly.

26:36.867 --> 26:38.133
It's harmful.

26:38.133 --> 26:41.233
- That's--
that is a guaranteed way

26:41.233 --> 26:43.333
to calm
the Chinese government down,

26:43.333 --> 26:46.367
to tell them they're not using
the human brain properly.

26:46.367 --> 26:47.700
- I told them,

26:47.700 --> 26:50.033
our brain usually, you see,

26:50.033 --> 26:53.567
have the ability
to create common sense.

26:53.567 --> 26:57.266
The Chinese hardliners,
in their brain,

26:57.266 --> 26:58.900
that part of brain is missing.

26:58.900 --> 27:01.200
- Zing.

27:01.200 --> 27:03.066
- But you know what I think?

27:03.066 --> 27:06.333
The Chinese leaders,
Chinese Communists,

27:06.333 --> 27:08.934
they are very much concerned
about image of China.

27:08.934 --> 27:11.700
- I'm happy to sit here
and criticize China with you,

27:11.700 --> 27:13.900
because I know
the consequences for me

27:13.900 --> 27:16.333
are not necessarily as bad
as they are for you.

27:16.333 --> 27:19.433
- [laughs]

27:19.433 --> 27:23.533
So, so I wish--
you see, they call me demon,

27:23.533 --> 27:26.033
so I want another demon,

27:26.033 --> 27:27.300
so you become demon.

27:27.300 --> 27:28.934
- No, no, no.
You can't transfer--

27:28.934 --> 27:31.400
you can't reincarnate the demon
into me.

27:31.400 --> 27:32.433
- Oh, yes, yes.

27:32.433 --> 27:33.433
- No, no, no, no.

27:33.433 --> 27:34.567
Don't make me a demon.

27:34.567 --> 27:36.133
- [laughs]
- No, no, no.

27:36.133 --> 27:38.266
You can't do--
we--you cannot do that.

27:38.266 --> 27:39.166
- You know...
- Can he do that?

27:39.166 --> 27:40.600
- As I've been telling you,
you see.

27:40.600 --> 27:43.333
- Oh, no.
- [laughs]

27:43.333 --> 27:45.266
- This is not how I wanted
this interview to go.

27:45.266 --> 27:47.367
So the Dalai Lama
seems determined

27:47.367 --> 27:50.834
to keep his reincarnation plans
private for the time being,

27:50.834 --> 27:53.633
leaving millions of Tibetans
waiting for an answer,

27:53.633 --> 27:55.133
and as our time drew
to a close,

27:55.133 --> 27:57.767
I wanted to cement
our new friendship.

27:57.767 --> 28:00.800
You were given a watch by
President Roosevelt.

28:00.800 --> 28:02.400
Is that true?
- Yes, true.

28:02.400 --> 28:06.734
At that time, I think one...
Patek Philippe.

28:06.734 --> 28:08.734
- Patek Philippe.
A beautiful watch.

28:08.734 --> 28:09.834
- Pocket watch.
- Right.

28:09.834 --> 28:13.066
Well, I have
a special gift for you.

28:13.066 --> 28:16.133
It is not a beautiful watch
from a president,

28:16.133 --> 28:19.233
but it is a special watch
from me.

28:19.233 --> 28:21.066
Here it is.

28:21.066 --> 28:22.967
It's a calculator watch.

28:22.967 --> 28:25.066
- Ah.

28:25.066 --> 28:26.033
- Right?

28:26.033 --> 28:27.033
- Oh.

28:27.033 --> 28:28.900
- Roosevelt may have given you
a fancy watch,

28:28.900 --> 28:31.433
but that is water-resistant.

28:31.433 --> 28:33.066
- Wonderful.
Thank you.

28:33.066 --> 28:36.734
Roosevelt watch,
I think, old-fashioned.

28:36.734 --> 28:38.533
- Yeah.
- Now this new-fashioned.

28:38.533 --> 28:41.400
- Well, not so much
new-fashioned as from the 1980s.

28:41.400 --> 28:42.533
- Thank you.

28:42.533 --> 28:43.600
Thank you.
Thank you much.

28:43.600 --> 28:44.700
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

28:44.700 --> 28:45.834
- My demon friend.

28:45.834 --> 28:48.300
- [laughs]
- It was an honor.

